          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  A <html:strong>sieve</html:strong> over an object <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> of an arbitrary category <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> is a subfunctor of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathop {\mkern {-2mu}\text {よ}\mkern {-2mu}}(A)]]></fr:tex>. More explicitly, it selects some arrows with codomain <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, such that the selected arrows absorbs composition (i.e. if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : B \to  A]]></fr:tex> is selected and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g : C \to  B]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g \mathbin {\circ } f]]></fr:tex> is also selected).
